SIMPLE: hammerhead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hammerhead
<hw>Ham"mer*head`</hw> <pr>(-h⟦ecr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A shark of the genus <gen>Sphyrna</gen> or
<gen>Zygaena</gen>, having the eyes set on projections from the sides of
the head, which gives it a hammer shape. The <spn>Sphyrna zygaena</spn>
is found in the North Atlantic. Called also <altname>hammer
fish</altname>, and <altname>balance fish</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 667 pr=JMD --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fresh-water fish; the
stone-roller.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An African fruit bat
(<spn>Hypsignathus monstrosus</spn>); -- so called from its large blunt
nozzle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hammerkop</ent>⟦br⟧
